align=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Ixiblat Fer</span><hr size=1> Last night our guild was trying to take out Ixiblat Fer for a few of our clerics. As expected spells weren't landing for diddly. A 600+ point shock of swords would hit at best for 250 damage or so. I cast malosi on him a total of 10 times between 3 fights and none of them stuck.<br>
<br>
My question is, does anybody know if the anti-summoned spells work against him? I know we'll be taking him out again so knowing a bit more about this guy would help.<br>
<br>
We're a fairly small guild and don't have a pocket full of 60's to come along so we're taking any strategies and pointers we can get for this guy. I noticed Banished Summoned does pretty good damge for the mana spent, just not sure it'll work against him.<br>
<br>
-Tweelis Twitchydigits<br>
-Echo of Valor, Saryrn<br>
-Level 54 Magician <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uepicureofquellious.showPublicProfile?language=EN>EpicureOfQuellious</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 63<br> <font color=#333333>(8/29/02 3:50:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1507.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Ixiblat Fer</span><hr size=1> I remember the next step down vs summoned worked on him when I was a young lad.  I would say with 90% certainty that yes, banish summoned would work.<br>
<br>
Epicure <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usolovey.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Solovey</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 50<br> <font color=#333333>(8/29/02 4:41:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1507.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://myweb.ecomplanet.com/COLL8955/mystorage/fireelemental.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Ixiblat Fer</span><hr size=1> Get your mages and druids to use your anti summoned lines they work and work well vs him...Also use your 49 fire pet it wont die against him as easily as the other pets do.<br>
<br>
Other then that if a class can atack at range tell them to do so :P rangers would be wise to use archery <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br>
<br>
Just got to stay on the heals and watch agro..If this guy ping pongs then you will all die :P. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ublipus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Blipus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#333333>(8/29/02 4:45:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1507.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Ixiblat Fer</span><hr size=1> Yes ,  equip all pets with rune swords and haste them up. use fire pets.  <br>
<br>
Anti summons nukes only on this guy.  <br>
<br>
oh and dispell his damage shield or it will own the pets as they, fire, are imune to his aoe fire attack.  pets dont draw agro with other melee there. <br>
<br>
We should have another Cazicserver mage hunt and whack this guy a few times for fun and loot,  i figure about 12 mages could own him in short order.  <br>
<br>
if pets only averaged 10 dmg a round thats like 120 dmg per melee round and then count the procs hehe if a 1/3rd hit thats 4x75? can remember what the sword procs hit for.  <br>
<br>
Just bag some muzzels and swords and chain a few pets.  think he melees for 500 so your gonna loose a pet every 3 rounds at leaste. Or toss a buff warrior in there to tank hehe.<br>
<br>
 <br>
<br>
<br>
